#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:4
msgid "Multiple Materials"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:6
msgid ""
"Normally, different colors or patterns on an object are achieved by "
"adding textures to your materials. However, in some applications you can "
"obtain multiple colors on an object by assigning different materials to "
"the individual faces of the object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:14
msgid "Add new material."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:17
msgid ""
"To apply several materials to different faces of the same object, you use"
" the Material Slots options (3) in the Materials header panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:23
msgid "Material menu in edit mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:26
msgid ""
"The workflow for applying a second material to some faces of an object "
"covered by a base material is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:30
msgid ""
"In Object mode, apply the base material to the whole object (as shown in "
":doc:`Assigning a material "
"</render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material>`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:32
msgid ""
"Create/select the second material (the whole object will change to this "
"new material)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:33
msgid "In the Active Material box (2), re-select the base material."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:34
msgid ""
"Go to Edit Mode - Face Select (a new box appears above the Active "
"Material box with Assign/Select/Deselect)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:35
msgid "Select the face/faces to be colored with the second material."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:36
msgid ""
"In the Object Material Slots box (3), click the :kbd:`Plus` to create a "
"new slot, and while this is still active, click on the second material in"
" the Available Materials list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:38
msgid ""
"Click the Assign button, and the second material will appear on the "
"selected object faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:41
msgid ""
"You can also make this new material a copy of an existing material by "
"adding the data block:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/multiple_materials.rst:43
msgid ""
"Select object, get the material, (R Click) - Copy data to clipboard. When"
" you have renamed the material, click \"Data - Data\" to link to the "
"existing material. Proceed to assign faces as required. NB: If you change"
" the material on the original object, the new object color changes too."
msgstr ""

